CAPE TOWN, January 16 – Janusz Walus, the man who murdered Chris Hani, was again denied parole on Wednesday. Justice Minister Michael Masutha said he had asked that further reports on Walus’ frame of mind be submitted in six months. Masutha stressed that Walus’ political views had not changed, though he showed remorse for the grief he inflicted on the family of Hani. (ANA)